00:25:08.580 --> 00:25:10.446
I met a lot of great people.

00:25:10.580 --> 00:25:11.656
Avner Goren who is the archeologist,
who I travel with both in the book

00:25:14.170 --> 00:25:15.933
and the television, so we are
still very close, actually he was

00:25:16.540 --> 00:25:18.673
at our home earlier this summer.

00:25:19.470 --> 00:25:20.536
Father, to those of you
who have read the book,

00:25:21.470 --> 00:25:24.403
Father Justin who is
the Texas monk who lives

00:25:24.920 --> 00:25:25.590
at St. Catherine has now
become the chief librarian.

00:25:27.650 --> 00:25:30.850
And I actually list his
email address in the book

00:25:31.150 --> 00:25:31.656
because there is a Burning
Bush there in St. Catherine's

00:25:34.310 --> 00:25:35.206
and there is a very memorable scene
in the book when I first arrived

00:25:37.880 --> 00:25:38.413
at St. Catherine which
is in the Sinai,

00:25:39.880 --> 00:25:43.546
which is where the monk say
the original Mount Sinai was

00:25:43.600 --> 00:25:44.933
and there is a bush.

00:25:45.600 --> 00:25:46.133
It is actually a rare
raspberry bramble

00:25:47.600 --> 00:25:48.276
that the monk say is
the actual Burning Bush

00:25:49.790 --> 00:25:50.416
where Moses saw the Face of
God and right next to this bush

00:25:53.030 --> 00:25:56.496
which is kind of is a big
kind of weeping willow kind

00:25:57.280 --> 00:25:59.413
of thing is a fire extinguisher.

00:25:59.740 --> 00:26:00.020
And the first time I saw it,
I thought is this an eye sore

00:26:03.260 --> 00:26:03.660
and then I realized the unintended--

00:26:05.260 --> 00:26:06.933
is this in case the Burning Bush
catches on fire and if it does catch

00:26:08.120 --> 00:26:12.320
on fire, do I look for the Face
of God or do I put the fire out.

00:26:13.450 --> 00:26:14.500
And years later when we
went to make the TV show,

00:26:15.600 --> 00:26:15.920
we filmed a little sequence with
me and the fire extinguisher

00:26:19.280 --> 00:26:20.100
and we sent it back to L.A. to
be edited and the editors took

00:26:22.460 --> 00:26:24.193
out the fire extinguisher.

00:26:24.460 --> 00:26:26.193
And when the draft came out,
I was like, why did you take

00:26:26.460 --> 00:26:28.060
out the fire extinguisher,
they said, you made that up.

00:26:28.460 --> 00:26:29.793
That's just a really bad
joke and you made that up.

00:26:30.460 --> 00:26:31.860
I was like no, no, no, I
didn't make that up at all.

00:26:32.460 --> 00:26:32.563
So, I am still in touch with Father
Justin and a lot of those people.

00:26:36.890 --> 00:26:38.163
And that journey does continue
in the book, Where God Was Born,

00:26:39.750 --> 00:26:41.143
which was what I talked about
the last time I was here

00:26:41.890 --> 00:26:44.106
and I was just actually in for those
of you who have come in designing,

00:26:44.340 --> 00:26:45.446
we actually have tons of copies
of Abraham, Walking the Bible,

00:26:47.300 --> 00:26:47.833
Where God Was Born,
America's Prophets,

00:26:49.300 --> 00:26:51.300
they have all that stuff here.

00:26:51.300 --> 00:26:52.300
Yes sir.

00:26:53.300 --> 00:26:54.033
&gt;&gt; I am just curious
if the travel program

00:26:55.300 --> 00:26:56.783
from Vermont was the experiment
in International Living and if so,

00:26:58.150 --> 00:26:59.223
do you have a brief commercial for
it or describe the actual program.

00:27:01.610 --> 00:27:02.810
&gt;&gt; The experiment for
International Living is one

00:27:03.610 --> 00:27:05.476
out of Brattleboro, Vermont.

00:27:05.610 --> 00:27:07.010
Actually, I will be in
Brattleboro a week from today

00:27:07.610 --> 00:27:08.010
at the Brattleboro
Literary Festival.

00:27:09.610 --> 00:27:10.010
This has come out-- is one of Putney

00:27:11.610 --> 00:27:12.410
in Vermont is called
Putney Student Travel.

00:27:13.610 --> 00:27:14.253
So, it is a smaller family
run operation that has been

00:27:16.500 --> 00:27:17.260
in the same family for 50
years and it is fantastic.

00:27:19.140 --> 00:27:21.740
Go Putney.com I would
give it an ad too,

00:27:22.080 --> 00:27:22.686
but it is the same
spirit as the experiment.

00:27:24.340 --> 00:27:25.643
Yes sir, we got-- they are
giving me a minute here.

00:27:26.370 --> 00:27:26.933
&gt;&gt; Sure, any suggestion for
somebody with some similar ideas

00:27:29.740 --> 00:27:29.773
to start writing their own book.

00:27:31.840 --> 00:27:32.543
&gt;&gt; Well, I am a big believer in,
you know, for aspiring writers

00:27:35.270 --> 00:27:35.703
that the most important
thing is to write.

00:27:37.570 --> 00:27:38.366
I find in talking to people that
there are a lot of aspiring writers

00:27:41.240 --> 00:27:42.990
who are a lot better at aspiring
than they are at writing.

00:27:43.290 --> 00:27:47.556
When I was in college I went to
see William Baldwin speak at Yale

00:27:48.110 --> 00:27:49.270
and he said, you want to be a
writer kid, you know, get a chair,

00:27:51.150 --> 00:27:52.433
get a table, get a piece of paper
and get a pen and start writing.

00:27:54.200 --> 00:27:54.503
I actually think that, you know,
when I went to Japan 20 years ago

00:27:58.230 --> 00:27:58.386
and started writing letters
home on crankily airmail paper,

00:28:01.940 --> 00:28:02.960
I think that the barriers to entry
were actually a lot higher then,

00:28:05.320 --> 00:28:05.866
so I think we have to be seen
now with blogging, with, I mean,

00:28:08.840 --> 00:28:10.373
there's any newspapers,

00:28:10.840 --> 00:28:12.566
The Washington Post not least among
them having written three pieces

00:28:13.580 --> 00:28:14.780
free for them in the last
month, that they will--

00:28:15.580 --> 00:28:16.113
a lot of people will
take free content.

00:28:17.580 --> 00:28:19.556
And so, I think that the most
important thing is to get published

00:28:19.870 --> 00:28:24.536
and it can be a church newsletter,
it can be a blog, it can be a letter

00:28:25.220 --> 00:28:26.286
that gets circulated to
friends because I think

00:28:27.220 --> 00:28:28.133
that the most important thing is to
get into the active communication

00:28:30.840 --> 00:28:31.566
and so, that you start
showing your writing.

00:28:32.980 --> 00:28:33.936
I think journaling is fine and has
had a lot of value to me and lots

00:28:36.490 --> 00:28:37.913
of people over the years, but
ultimately, I think writing is

00:28:39.000 --> 00:28:40.933
about communication and I was

00:28:41.000 --> 00:28:42.933
in the media earlier saying
what does it mean to you to come

00:28:43.000 --> 00:28:44.566
to the National Book Festival
and I said, it means to me

00:28:45.100 --> 00:28:45.886
to be reminded ultimately that
this is about communication,

00:28:48.180 --> 00:28:48.870
to have writers in touch with
readers, having feedback,

00:28:51.090 --> 00:28:52.756
that is what it is about.

00:28:53.090 --> 00:28:53.276
So, I am delighted to be here to
share the story with all of you.

00:28:57.170 --> 00:28:58.090
If you want to email me, you
can go to brucefeiler.com.

00:28:59.850 --> 00:28:59.886
I answer every email that
comes and happy reading.

00:29:03.080 --> 00:29:04.413
Thank you very much.

